<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10034i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10034i">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10034i"> 34(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> beast of burden</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Les courriers du temps de l&apos;empire avaient le droit de forcer les particuliers et les villes &agrave; leur fournir des chevaux ou des b&ecirc;tes de somme, quelquefois des voitures, comme nous l&apos;apprend le juriconsulte Paulus, au mot <i>Angari&aelig;</i>. <font color="green">[In the time of the empire, the couriers had the right to force individuals and cities to give them horses or beasts of burden, sometimes even vehicles, as we know from the jurist consul Paulus, under the term <i>Angari&aelig;</i>]</font> <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) 37</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
